[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# Using Grid in HTML & CSS\n\nIn this example we will look into how grid can be used to layout your project.\n\n## Seting up the HTML\n\nFirst we want to create the HTML. For that we create a `main` element and add a `container` class to it. Inside the container, we add six items. All items are simple `div` elements with the class `item` and an individual class applied."},{"kind":2,"language":"html","value":"<main class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"item item1\">1. Item</div>\n  <div class=\"item item2\">2. Item</div>\n  <div class=\"item item3\">3. Item</div>\n  <div class=\"item item4\">4. Item</div>\n  <div class=\"item item5\">5. Item</div>\n  <div class=\"item item6\">6. Item</div>\n</main>"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Setting up the CSS\n\nNext, we want to setup the CSS. We create the `container` class in CSS and set the `display` value to `grid`."},{"kind":2,"language":"css","value":".container {\n  display: grid;\n}"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"As you can see, nothing happens to our output. So next, we want to set the number of columns our grid should have. In this case, we want to set the property `grid-template-columns` to `1fr 1fr 1fr`. This will create a grid that contains 3 columns and each column has a width of 1 fraction, in this case, 1/3 of the full width."},{"kind":2,"language":"css","value":".container {\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);\n}"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"To visualize it a bit more, we want to set the border of every item to be `1px`, `solid`, and have the color `#000000`."},{"kind":2,"language":"css","value":".item {\n  border: 1px solid #000000;\n}"},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"Next we want to set the height of the rows to be 40px."},{"kind":2,"language":"css","value":".container {\n  grid-auto-rows: 40px;\n}"}]